  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>For breakfast you'll have a hot and cold buffet with various options.</p>
<p>When it comes to supper you'll have a three course meal including an antipasti and salad buffet. The hotel's known for its food, especially its traditional Italian dishes, so you won't be disappointed.</p>
<p><strong>Gordon's Pub </strong>is an Irish pub attached to the hotel, open every day. This is a great place for après or grabbing a bite to eat and has regular entertainment and happy hour.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Chalet du Lys is right at the bottom of the Sant'Anna ski slope against a stunning back drop of the Monte Rosa Massif mountain range. It's a fantastic family friendly hotel with a playroom and games to keep the children busy. The décor is a cosy Alpine style and the daily live pianist adds to the hotels lovely ambiance.</p>
<h2>Close to the slopes</h2>
<p>The cosy Chalet du Lys benefits from being at the foot of the Sant Anna ski slopes in the Stafal area of <a data-udi="umb://document/df8adba64dd44f3c87eb2df1c821a98e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/df8adba64dd44f3c87eb2df1c821a98e}" title="Gressoney">Gressoney,</a> you can easily start and end or your day. The lifts are only 150 metres away, and you can ski back to the hotel on your return. The quaint village of Gressoney is a short bus ride away, or you can venture down on the winding red run down into the village. </p>
<h2>Bar and spa</h2>
<p>When you're hungry, the hotel's got a great reputation for its typical Italian food in La Grange, and on Monday evenings, be sure to head down a little earlier to enjoy an aperitivo, the perfect way to end the day. Those of you who like a little après, head to the Irish pub next door ' Gorodns Pub'- it couldn't be more convenient - plus on Friday evenings there is often live music. </p>
<p>After a day on the slopes, there is nowhere better to unwind than in the Lys Spa - it really is the perfect antidote to any achy ski legs. Enjoy the Turkish bath, sauna, salt room and chromotherapy showers, before relaxing in the relaxation area with a herbal tea. For an additional fee, treat yourself to a massage with one of the therapists. You can also make the most of the heated outdoor pool and take in the stunning views of the glacier.</p>]]></description>
